CodeRabbit Review — Phase 5+6 commit (36377a9)
================================================

## Potential Issues (10 findings)

### Accessibility
1. Header share icon not keyboard accessible (Header.jsx:22)
   — The <img onClick> should be wrapped in a <button> for keyboard/screen-reader users.

### Defensive coding (pre-existing patterns)
2. No response.ok check in fetchList (store.js:105-120)
   — Non-2xx responses could corrupt shoppingItems.
3. No response.ok check in storeList (store.js:122-135)
   — Same issue for POST.
4. shoppingItems could be undefined (Button.jsx:50-55, SortableList.jsx:92-101)
   — During hydration, .length / .map() could throw. Suggests optional chaining or || [] fallback.

### Error handling (pre-existing patterns)
5. No error handling for shareList (Header.jsx:13-17)
   — Async API call with no catch.
6. No error handling for startListening (Button.jsx:26-35)
   — Speech recognition failure gives no feedback.

### Data uniqueness
7. item.name used as sortable ID (SortableList.jsx:27-30)
   — Duplicate names would break dnd-kit and React keys.
8. findIndex by name in drag handler (SortableList.jsx:83-85)
   — Same uniqueness concern.

### Test quality
9. Shared test fixture by reference (store.test.js:3-7)
   — Could cause test pollution if store mutates objects. Suggests factory function.

### Response validation
10. storeList POST has no response validation (store.js:122-135)
    — No response.ok check, successful saves go unacknowledged.

---
Notes:
- Most findings are pre-existing patterns carried over from the old Redux code.
- The shoppingItems undefined guard is unnecessary since Zustand initializes it
  as an array and persist uses a merge function, but || [] is low-cost insurance.
- The accessibility finding and test fixture suggestion are actionable improvements.
